# CaptionDB Testing Engineering Contract

## Purpose

This contract defines the mandatory testing strategy for CaptionDB.

Testing is a required engineering activity.

No feature is considered complete until it has been appropriately tested.

---

# Testing Philosophy

Tests prove correctness.

Tests protect against regression.

Tests improve confidence.

Tests should be:

Reliable

Repeatable

Fast

Independent

Readable

Maintainable

---

# Testing Pyramid

Follow the testing pyramid.

Unit Tests

↓

Integration Tests

↓

End-to-End Tests

Most tests should be unit tests.

Avoid excessive E2E tests.

---

# Test Categories

The project should include:

- Unit Tests
- Integration Tests
- API Tests
- Performance Tests
- Load Tests
- Regression Tests
- Smoke Tests
- Security Tests
- UI Tests (Frontend)
- End-to-End Tests

---

# Unit Testing

Every service should support isolated testing.

Mock external dependencies.

Never call:

Fireworks

OCR

Scene Detection

External APIs

during unit tests.

Unit tests should execute quickly.

---

# Integration Testing

Integration tests verify interaction between modules.

Examples:

Pipeline + Fireworks Client (Mock)

API + Services

Export + Pipeline

Configuration + Application

---

# End-to-End Testing

E2E tests validate complete workflows.

Example:

Upload Video

↓

Processing

↓

Caption Generation

↓

Export

↓

Download

Use representative sample videos.

---

# Test Isolation

Every test should be independent.

Avoid:

Shared state

Shared files

Shared configuration

Order-dependent execution

Tests should pass regardless of execution order.

---

# Test Naming

Use descriptive names.

Good:

test_generate_caption_returns_structured_output

test_invalid_video_is_rejected

Bad:

test1

test_api

---

# Mocking

Mock:

Fireworks

OCR

Filesystem

Network

Time

Environment Variables

Never depend on external services during automated testing.

---

# Fixtures

Use reusable fixtures.

Avoid duplicated setup.

Fixtures should remain focused.

Do not create giant fixtures.

---

# Assertions

Assertions should verify behavior.

Avoid testing implementation details.

Test observable outcomes.

---

# Coverage

Aim for high coverage of business logic.

Focus especially on:

Services

Pipeline

Validation

Utilities

Configuration

Avoid writing meaningless tests solely to increase coverage.

---

# Edge Cases

Every feature should test:

Empty input

Invalid input

Large input

Unexpected input

Boundary values

Timeouts

Retries

Failures

---

# Exception Testing

Verify:

Correct exception type

Correct error message

Correct logging

Graceful recovery

---

# API Testing

Test:

Request validation

Response validation

Status codes

Headers

Error responses

OpenAPI schema consistency

---

# Frontend Testing

Frontend should include:

Component Tests

Hook Tests

Interaction Tests

Accessibility Tests

API Mock Tests

Avoid coupling tests to backend implementation.

---

# Snapshot Testing

Use snapshots sparingly.

Only for stable UI components.

Do not overuse snapshots.

---

# Performance Testing

Measure:

Latency

Memory

CPU

Throughput

Processing Time

Compare benchmark results before and after optimizations.

---

# Load Testing

Support future load testing.

Test:

Concurrent uploads

Concurrent caption generation

Queue behavior

Resource limits

---

# Regression Testing

Every bug fix should include a regression test.

Prevent the same bug from reappearing.

---

# Smoke Testing

Verify:

Application starts

Configuration loads

Health endpoint responds

Pipeline initializes

Critical services available

Run smoke tests after deployment.

---

# Security Testing

Verify:

Input validation

Path traversal protection

File upload validation

Authentication (future)

Authorization (future)

Secret handling

---

# Test Data

Use representative test data.

Avoid using production secrets.

Store test assets separately.

Document large test files.

---

# Temporary Files

Tests must clean temporary files.

Avoid leaving artifacts after execution.

---

# Deterministic Tests

Tests should produce identical results.

Avoid randomness.

If randomness is required, use fixed seeds.

---

# CI Compatibility

All automated tests should run inside CI.

Tests must not require manual interaction.

Tests should fail clearly.

---

# Failure Messages

Assertion failures should explain:

Expected

Actual

Reason

Avoid vague failures.

---

# Code Quality

Testing is not a substitute for code review.

Poor architecture cannot be fixed by more tests.

---

# Documentation

Document:

Test strategy

How to run tests

Required dependencies

Mock strategy

Coverage expectations

---

# Test Review Checklist

Before completing implementation verify:

✓ Unit tests added

✓ Integration tests updated

✓ Edge cases covered

✓ Exceptions tested

✓ Mocks used appropriately

✓ API responses tested

✓ Temporary files cleaned

✓ Performance considered

✓ Security scenarios tested

✓ CI compatible

✓ Documentation updated

If any item fails, revise implementation before completion.

---

End of Testing Engineering Contract.
